Steps to do Karma Setup - 
- Install Node
- npm init (to create package.json)
- npm install karma karma-coverage --save-dev (karma coverage for generating reports)
- npm install -g karma-cli (if need to use command prompt)
- npm install karma-jasmine jasmine-core karma-chrome-launcher --save-dev (enable  jasmine for karma and make chrome as target browser)
- create a folder and place test files 
- karma init (to configure karma settings)
- npm install angular angular-mocks --save-dev
- update the files section with the files in scope

to Generate report, Karma uses istanbul
we need t o configure 2 things to enabme generating report 
- set the scope of the files for coverage in 'preprocessor' property of karma config file
- set the 'reporter' property as 'coverage'

-- Run 'karma start'
